{"type":"message","id":"ad06535d","parentId":"c6948f44","timestamp":"2026-04-25T12:36:41.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Creating a transcription script**\n\nI need to create a script and test it on sample audio. I'll write it as `bin/transcribe_voice.py` and consider using a tiny model for speed. It might allow for a path argument to output text. I should set up a model download for the first run.\n\nI’ll document this in TOOLS or a README, but specifics may not be necessary. The goal is to verify the transcription on the attached OGG file, which might take time due to the model download. Keeping it simple is key!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0e249c009ade638f0169ecb54d0c8c8191aef21768e2a0dcd3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp7LVS9TvmtonGTXiXV4trpe4fs8wj7lp-_1g15kmcBEDcV-i5lEmjnqMYjNGYcoLY4BJBCtKl5cUlf6JXsYldOXcjs-GcSmvvS3OspZlvPauhhsmUIO-ogsZwCtWHSQolhCwXl5koDNThFPiRetKxT9M2nLnuV1NkiQYQq-RULCUVwnDvxNB0N-kZHPNNw-9mqR6LmXPXw_N0xjiIFy__pqb3qvSqs7AmkeRGkMpZlQxTTad0WgL54XfFRG6FECyW-nMrhd_2Jfe7IQ_cfxwN0A6H5zzXp_O9Ee7YUfTNTMnRUKYjK6KHSg4ex0UNT9nDupPfOCesi6RjE0fdwMQlu24TzLxplyRpgH4CRy6LtM3srd2ZQL2dTkuYtifPGofdyPV5EygDYz1cZZDcdoA1-1m018WY7NaPOK5lwfiN4Eb47U8oCTzYDDKMkBgA1PeWvaYSJyf_I2dS9TmeATmwk94NLYeqS82MLcNTnN84kt5rZrU0lF3L-dtJVBacUPaM-noFJe786L15end6fR4bdnLMR_WtxVFGq5PAg5O7M58WEFXbjedIOlbMYoCoFzV0NEtJmMEOH-9KUswCPxrulohSUtq_IQmc52chpp1zlqvG7XQ7m4NbdjeljYTipuL0UYS2G-WxOXAqH7vJvKG-fcNSLYxJN5pWvM79lAIROi-as4DUAXnqiq8KGjZZljd1sNG6tlL0niT5K9qz13JWvrQALALTV33kvATzoZyyPG65zvv6uINT_dNKUbXrjQXhDm_fmUAQ45D57oLmdpoZzHh9rxwbvYtcK9sscQd3eNVWlv4BojCiEEz-MiRpwvBASB-5HxGeHtUVBMHT_C1rlAyo5G6F9wzcLMf9T7fJYB-g0n7XgLqnsE05-xZyThXt2Y2RpVXXlbtNxpw9_qw90hJY6CWb5OacO4GIbzN4zn0dTDaP76EUFHej8wIMmf6CPssYtpYD30uhJJavBHdpS78iREryrq6bNJa0aFQCVF7h62BhP47L6Sv1hwx3R4nC7UAR4qrAiALXJUQufcM6AyrWEpDLgUV-zLbdRFwOTHKNKODf4lmBumR6dlKZ661Bw28C1MB2xPZA3jTjnTOXc61OwK3Xbhnf-e3V0iYYCC6axeRtEXtvXJXBr25F5jB7zeKf1V4gNM8HXeIciQaZNNtRmtxjx5jOqhnH6VeIZzyv3EVE2hNr-ySkXjrhbV8Gd_2GHvsrG4OaDKMqbb2VGYhU4K9hbvPVULqWnRnVx5XtyEPdVaZdFnFR5fdT0p7IoAmClEYa1dOlKPtxIF5j3zyGMh01LqdE8l7FqTjYnTKFCdQEuqbfxhPP5v4DzB-zwB2mgP5T57Pfb4O9Wd1zxNi5Wrk78D8AnblAVGE4THbNxa_xg9obcJpvB81B-O58ZruQ5k837s7amU6IIE-GfjyRcM4kcYXREdOPr3kl24DSptidKv5ld9c4i4FKYqmUSQq8uxSEHOREgczoaeVHyUKTvmPaPa6iM_qICHwOFs5a1q2I5gBfIdmBlkYZ4Yqwcc3yvBvJhnvMvwgcDO2uhxAdwDlZoDkvyYCKr_4ksMxJ5WY=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating a transcription script**\\n\\nI need to create a script and test it on sample audio. I'll write it as `bin/transcribe_voice.py` and consider using a tiny model for speed. It might allow for a path argument to output text. I should set up a model download for the first run.\\n\\nI’ll document this in TOOLS or a README, but specifics may not be necessary. The goal is to verify the transcription on the attached OGG file, which might take time due to the model download. Keeping it simple is key!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_WJuR7rnFpraKou9FVyMfzvU6|fc_0e249c009ade638f0169ecb552ac488191819026367465fbbe","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/transcribe_voice.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom faster_whisper import WhisperModel\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Transcribe an audio file with faster-whisper\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"audio\", help=\"Path to the audio file\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--model\", default=\"tiny\", help=\"Whisper model size (default: tiny)\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--language\", default=None, help=\"Optional language code, e.g. en, zh, ms\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--task\", default=\"transcribe\", choices=[\"transcribe\", \"translate\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--json\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Emit JSON\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    audio_path = Path(args.audio)\n    if not audio_path.exists():\n        print(f\"Audio file not found: {audio_path}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 1\n\n    model = WhisperModel(args.model, device=\"cpu\", compute_type=\"int8\")\n    segments, info = model.transcribe(\n        str(audio_path),\n        language=args.language,\n        task=args.task,\n        vad_filter=True,\n    )\n\n    parts = []\n    segment_rows = []\n    for segment in segments:\n        text = segment.text.strip()\n        if not text:\n            continue\n        parts.append(text)\n        segment_rows.append(\n            {\n                \"start\": round(segment.start, 2),\n                \"end\": round(segment.end, 2),\n                \"text\": text,\n            }\n        )\n\n    text = \" \".join(parts).strip()\n    payload = {\n        \"file\": str(audio_path),\n        \"language\": info.language,\n        \"language_probability\": round(info.language_probability, 4),\n        \"duration\": round(info.duration, 2),\n        \"text\": text,\n        \"segments\": segment_rows,\n    }\n\n    if args.json:\n        print(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n    else:\n        print(text)\n\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    raise SystemExit(main())\n"}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":988,"output":664,"cacheRead":43904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45556,"cost":{"input":0.0024700000000000004,"output":0.00996,"cacheRead":0.010976,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023406}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777120587836,"responseId":"resp_0e249c009ade638f0169ecb54c1e308191a920db67de833c2a"}}
