{"type":"message","id":"5c593032","parentId":"b8f7d6b8","timestamp":"2026-04-25T13:18:14.529Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_rqJqnh8PBJYXHtICPc9Yd4Ws|fc_0e249c009ade638f0169ecbf160d788191aa1707aa03eea337","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.23 (a979721) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw webhooks gmail setup [options]\n\nConfigure Gmail watch + Pub/Sub + OpenClaw hooks\n\nOptions:\n  --account <email>            Gmail account to watch\n  --bind <host>                gog watch serve bind host (default: \"127.0.0.1\")\n  -h, --help                   Display help for command\n  --hook-token <token>         OpenClaw hook token\n  --hook-url <url>             OpenClaw hook URL\n  --include-body               Include email body snippets (default: true)\n  --json                       Output JSON summary (default: false)\n  --label <label>              Gmail label to watch (default: \"INBOX\")\n  --max-bytes <n>              Max bytes for body snippets (default: \"20000\")\n  --path <path>                gog watch serve path (default: \"/gmail-pubsub\")\n  --port <port>                gog watch serve port (default: \"8788\")\n  --project <id>               GCP project id (OAuth client owner)\n  --push-endpoint <url>        Explicit Pub/Sub push endpoint\n  --push-token <token>         Push token for gog watch serve\n  --renew-minutes <n>          Renew watch every N minutes (default: \"720\")\n  --subscription <name>        Pub/Sub subscription name (default:\n                               \"gog-gmail-watch-push\")\n  --tailscale <mode>           Expose push endpoint via tailscale\n                               (funnel|serve|off) (default: \"funnel\")\n  --tailscale-path <path>      Path for tailscale serve/funnel\n  --tailscale-target <target>  Tailscale serve/funnel target (port, host:port,\n                               or URL)\n  --topic <name>               Pub/Sub topic name (default: \"gog-gmail-watch\")\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tender-cedar","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.23 (a979721) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw webhooks gmail setup [options]\n\nConfigure Gmail watch + Pub/Sub + OpenClaw hooks\n\nOptions:\n  --account <email>            Gmail account to watch\n  --bind <host>                gog watch serve bind host (default: \"127.0.0.1\")\n  -h, --help                   Display help for command\n  --hook-token <token>         OpenClaw hook token\n  --hook-url <url>             OpenClaw hook URL\n  --include-body               Include email body snippets (default: true)\n  --json                       Output JSON summary (default: false)\n  --label <label>              Gmail label to watch (default: \"INBOX\")\n  --max-bytes <n>              Max bytes for body snippets (default: \"20000\")\n  --path <path>                gog watch serve path (default: \"/gmail-pubsub\")\n  --port <port>                gog watch serve port (default: \"8788\")\n  --project <id>               GCP project id (OAuth client owner)\n  --push-endpoint <url>        Explicit Pub/Sub push endpoint\n  --push-token <token>         Push token for gog watch serve\n  --renew-minutes <n>          Renew watch every N minutes (default: \"720\")\n  --subscription <name>        Pub/Sub subscription name (default:\n                               \"gog-gmail-watch-push\")\n  --tailscale <mode>           Expose push endpoint via tailscale\n                               (funnel|serve|off) (default: \"funnel\")\n  --tailscale-path <path>      Path for tailscale serve/funnel\n  --tailscale-target <target>  Tailscale serve/funnel target (port, host:port,\n                               or URL)\n  --topic <name>               Pub/Sub topic name (default: \"gog-gmail-watch\")\n","name":"openclaw webhooks"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777123094529}}
