{"type":"message","id":"e8c92336","parentId":"fc7faa75","timestamp":"2026-04-25T13:29:14.442Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_wHw7tpJu9UDWwTNONfmApNg8|fc_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc1aa2b248191b4ea2918601e87dc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: gog auth add <email> [flags]\nBuild: v0.13.0 (5cd913e28780)\n\nAuthorize and store a refresh token\n\nArguments:\n  <email>    Email\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                    Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"            Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING          Account email for API commands\n                                (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript/ads)\n      --client=\"\"               OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                                token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING     Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                                stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n                                ($GOG_ACCESS_TOKEN)\n      --enable-commands=\"\"      Comma-separated list of enabled commands;\n                                dot paths allowed (restricts CLI)\n      --disable-commands=\"\"     Comma-separated list of disabled commands;\n                                dot paths allowed\n      --gmail-no-send           Block Gmail send operations (agent safety)\n  -j, --json                    Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)\n  -p, --plain                   Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;\n                                no colors)\n      --results-only            In JSON mode, emit only the primary result\n                                (drops envelope fields like nextPageToken)\n      --select=STRING           In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields\n                                (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:\n                                use --fields for most commands.\n  -n, --dry-run                 Do not make changes; print intended actions and\n                                exit successfully\n  -y, --force                   Skip confirmations for destructive commands\n      --no-input                Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)\n  -v, --verbose                 Enable verbose logging\n      --version                 Print version and exit\n\n      --manual                  Browserless auth flow (paste redirect URL)\n      --remote                  Remote/server-friendly manual flow (print URL,\n                                then exchange code)\n      --step=INT                Remote auth step: 1=print URL, 2=exchange code\n      --listen-addr=STRING      Address to listen on for OAuth callback (for\n                                example 0.0.0.0 or 0.0.0.0:8080)\n      --redirect-host=STRING    Hostname for OAuth callback in browser flows;\n                                builds https://{host}/oauth2/callback\n      --redirect-uri=STRING     Override OAuth redirect URI for\n                                manual/remote flows (for example\n                                https://host.example/oauth2/callback)\n      --auth-url=STRING         Redirect URL from browser (manual flow; required\n                                for --remote --step 2)\n      --timeout=DURATION        Authorization timeout (manual flows default to\n                                5m)\n      --force-consent           Force consent screen to obtain a refresh token\n      --services=\"user\"         Services to authorize:\n                                user|all or comma-separated\n                                gmail,calendar,chat,classroom,drive,docs,slides,contacts,tasks,sheets,people,forms,appscript,ads\n                                (Keep uses service account: gog auth\n                                service-account set)\n      --readonly                Use read-only scopes where available (still\n                                includes OIDC identity scopes)\n      --drive-scope=\"full\"      Drive scope mode: full|readonly|file\n      --gmail-scope=\"full\"      Gmail scope mode: full|readonly\n      --extra-scopes=STRING     Comma-separated list of additional OAuth scope\n                                URIs to request (appended after service scopes)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":91,"aggregated":"Usage: gog auth add <email> [flags]\nBuild: v0.13.0 (5cd913e28780)\n\nAuthorize and store a refresh token\n\nArguments:\n  <email>    Email\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                    Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"            Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING          Account email for API commands\n                                (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript/ads)\n      --client=\"\"               OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                                token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING     Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                                stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n                                ($GOG_ACCESS_TOKEN)\n      --enable-commands=\"\"      Comma-separated list of enabled commands;\n                                dot paths allowed (restricts CLI)\n      --disable-commands=\"\"     Comma-separated list of disabled commands;\n                                dot paths allowed\n      --gmail-no-send           Block Gmail send operations (agent safety)\n  -j, --json                    Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)\n  -p, --plain                   Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;\n                                no colors)\n      --results-only            In JSON mode, emit only the primary result\n                                (drops envelope fields like nextPageToken)\n      --select=STRING           In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields\n                                (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:\n                                use --fields for most commands.\n  -n, --dry-run                 Do not make changes; print intended actions and\n                                exit successfully\n  -y, --force                   Skip confirmations for destructive commands\n      --no-input                Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)\n  -v, --verbose                 Enable verbose logging\n      --version                 Print version and exit\n\n      --manual                  Browserless auth flow (paste redirect URL)\n      --remote                  Remote/server-friendly manual flow (print URL,\n                                then exchange code)\n      --step=INT                Remote auth step: 1=print URL, 2=exchange code\n      --listen-addr=STRING      Address to listen on for OAuth callback (for\n                                example 0.0.0.0 or 0.0.0.0:8080)\n      --redirect-host=STRING    Hostname for OAuth callback in browser flows;\n                                builds https://{host}/oauth2/callback\n      --redirect-uri=STRING     Override OAuth redirect URI for\n                                manual/remote flows (for example\n                                https://host.example/oauth2/callback)\n      --auth-url=STRING         Redirect URL from browser (manual flow; required\n                                for --remote --step 2)\n      --timeout=DURATION        Authorization timeout (manual flows default to\n                                5m)\n      --force-consent           Force consent screen to obtain a refresh token\n      --services=\"user\"         Services to authorize:\n                                user|all or comma-separated\n                                gmail,calendar,chat,classroom,drive,docs,slides,contacts,tasks,sheets,people,forms,appscript,ads\n                                (Keep uses service account: gog auth\n                                service-account set)\n      --readonly                Use read-only scopes where available (still\n                                includes OIDC identity scopes)\n      --drive-scope=\"full\"      Drive scope mode: full|readonly|file\n      --gmail-scope=\"full\"      Gmail scope mode: full|readonly\n      --extra-scopes=STRING     Comma-separated list of additional OAuth scope\n                                URIs to request (appended after service scopes)","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777123754442}}
