\n\nThe Google auth itself worked far enough to exchange the code, but it stopped on **secure local token storage**:\n`gog` wants a **keyring password** to encrypt the Gmail token on this machine.\n\nSo the only thing I need from you now is:\n\n**Choose a password for Gmail token storage**\n\nYou can send something like:\n`Use this keyring password: <your-password>`\n\nAfter that I can finish connecting Gmail.\n\nIf you’d rather not send a password in chat, I can instead help you do a more manual one-time setup on your side.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc217e170819180f78332a714023a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":637,"output":240,"cacheRead":78976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79853,"cost":{"input":0.0015925000000000002,"output":0.0036,"cacheRead":0.019743999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024936499999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777123859743,"responseId":"resp_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc21416cc81918bd486aaade8937d"}}
