{"type":"message","id":"aba10c0f","parentId":"cbcd1b99","timestamp":"2026-04-25T13:35:38.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering user preferences**\n\nI want to make sure my response is really helpful. I think we might not need any tools for this, but maybe I should check my memory for the user’s prior preferences since they seem to be successful. It could be good to guide them to the next steps, especially if something important might be unread. Since they likely want automatic access, I should mention that everything looks good, and they’re now connected. Keeping it concise will be key!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc31d3abc8191b868cf35b60ce33a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp7MMgbWpWePiqhTgYUY9G4GMaBh5u-voPdx3n3fiYEnLGzrCjo9vRn62WpgUyw0Brt9Elicx9RETfiKN9E-2kXrOXavhCs9i8e3Z4q3mxCU7BA7tSUYMbuOrPoo-nAPQfYqIBNLzMUGGnviqo-0A-7-RxTJpTeFN90PkVV2q_bfElQJ8DtKo3DW51OeoEu1YG51feXwhmvPFEGnRn8gKjuHcRqvE85sIIt7cqr4cb6GPz8-6DpfvLCL-q-26oaBXLFk7AebiG9I36cJCOMG2JV8lnC3-DZSKoEL1ydlZ9Gn19QC9xA2cAIMmu5p2XILDYT_2UzLaYUdv7PHwHSrJ5LmB_UQTM37IKz3yJedNluIT5I-vYnvPg5v90mCbjw9KFFTu6vStktCMw2KuS6GLqOaacqjyAfBXbnz2VEM_Q9PWOp-qworu98dTYdZiqvYmJIlL-bQFfSxhQPq0D1bXrGtPK8OuQALP2HM96QUmDAz1bEFUkyg3nLdXhnPHaSLsBvfCmbZYx8wXlU1L0Kpy5MI-fAzhWkPXbUk8eabv2zE8uFR_TIK6H_vMr21g8DVziHMPS_vKFGcHXoDtOlTgOQPUwwv_yNcjw85tivmCbIYU1EptIGke0VBAzxKpo618lgnRv6xmBZ1yaCkf6lSMS9d9OSquTPXdISVa6fU8mlmbNuhG7Vvo7rugQwDLFyKrNENzBtQaFh32N_N2_Inm3noLJOEP7pP78fc9-bpsDjsKfcHh4ys_23TmkpO89hZXyciUHqqB5NRJpHVuApikQzHt3V4TOddbi3ng3G5H70i4Jrt4C57vEsHqs8hUV-cuQbXP_dkwap38eChQRMNGyCIwzrLplznXp6-iIbJuxm0S7sL16t-AaFZbMGViAvQUqGRXB3VG_XC-JaXCnigmQzORI1R_C0QQThahbKm4pFqFnM4xSBwF42b3HLWnaqHYW4xPIUkez990bLgkVg1h20z271K9osrG9c6Fzxu1fKwO0oHRBX2mznm4_9vyZXKwXhWJFwctav9xOyQg4gUfedZKcqahXnZZVZ9BqFuFGZey1LE7E2ZHIdCE1nPV3f4HLFv2yTqnouEGd0G1akJp5yaj-0OdxB9QkdSn1lLB_9GdYXWQpbVLpzzHpEgUfLQsPAOg-Eu3OgBRFCq09B5hOhH6zpLsKSGh-gMQ15DIco7efkEYUSA1bBKXGrgki_7adEKxbt1g2WJqVRR_yD_T-Q-eE9_MkNuyR1Q-XaEpNMgedAUDqjY0P15-9x4A1nTzs1wnUPMkmLhysheTyV42OwEsuMw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering user preferences**\\n\\nI want to make sure my response is really helpful. I think we might not need any tools for this, but maybe I should check my memory for the user’s prior preferences since they seem to be successful. It could be good to guide them to the next steps, especially if something important might be unread. Since they likely want automatic access, I should mention that everything looks good, and they’re now connected. Keeping it concise will be key!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Nice — that worked. Gmail read-only access is live now. 🌙\n\nYou can already use it to check unread/important mail.\n\nTry these:\n\n**Unread emails**\n```bash\ngog --account xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx gmail threads list --query \"is:unread\" --limit 20\n```\n\n**Important unread**\n```bash\ngog --account xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx gmail threads list --query \"is:unread is:important\" --limit 20\n```\n\n**Unread in primary inbox only**\n```bash\ngog --account xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx gmail threads list --query \"in:inbox category:primary is:unread\" --limit 20\n```\n\n**See one thread in detail**\n```bash\ngog --account xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx gmail threads get <THREAD_ID>\n```\n\nIf you want, next I can help you set up one of these:\n\n1. **A simple command** to show only important unread mail  \n2. **An automatic Gmail watcher** for new unread emails  \n3. **A triage workflow** so I can help sort urgent vs ignore","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc320d56c8191b786cb6c1a36ea8e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":474,"output":300,"cacheRead":80256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81030,"cost":{"input":0.001185,"output":0.0045000000000000005,"cacheRead":0.020064,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025749}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777124123575,"responseId":"resp_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc31bf39081919a96bbcd57b41ded"}}
