{"type":"message","id":"55176a35","parentId":"8e1e4e5f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T13:37:14.422Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ezJjiffk7vD1OI0OPpT7dQrj|fc_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc38a18008191adecbbee372f2cbf","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: gog gmail (mail,email) <command> [flags]\nBuild: v0.13.0 (5cd913e28780)\n\nGmail\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"           Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING         Account email for API commands\n                               (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript/ads)\n      --client=\"\"              OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                               token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING    Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                               stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n                               ($GOG_ACCESS_TOKEN)\n      --enable-commands=\"\"     Comma-separated list of enabled commands;\n                               dot paths allowed (restricts CLI)\n      --disable-commands=\"\"    Comma-separated list of disabled commands;\n                               dot paths allowed\n      --gmail-no-send          Block Gmail send operations (agent safety)\n  -j, --json                   Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)\n  -p, --plain                  Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;\n                               no colors)\n      --results-only           In JSON mode, emit only the primary result (drops\n                               envelope fields like nextPageToken)\n      --select=STRING          In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields\n                               (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:\n                               use --fields for most commands.\n  -n, --dry-run                Do not make changes; print intended actions and\n                               exit successfully\n  -y, --force                  Skip confirmations for destructive commands\n      --no-input               Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)\n  -v, --verbose                Enable verbose logging\n      --version                Print version and exit\n\nRead\n  search (find,query,ls,list) <query> ... [flags]\n    Search threads using Gmail query syntax\n\n  messages (message,msg,msgs) search (find,query,ls,list) <query> ... [flags]\n    Search messages using Gmail query syntax\n\n  get (info,show) <messageId> [flags]\n    Get a message (full|metadata|raw)\n\n  attachment <messageId> <attachmentId> [flags]\n    Download a single attachment\n\n  url <threadId> ...\n    Print Gmail web URLs for threads\n\n  history [flags]\n    Gmail history\n\nOrganize\n  messages (message,msg,msgs) modify (update,edit,set) <messageId> [flags]\n    Modify labels on a single message\n\n  thread (threads,read) get (info,show) <threadId> [flags]\n    Get a thread with all messages (optionally download attachments)\n\n  thread (threads,read) modify (update,edit,set) <threadId> [flags]\n    Modify labels on all messages in a thread\n\n  thread (threads,read) attachments (files) <threadId> [flags]\n    List all attachments in a thread\n\n  labels (label) list (ls)\n    List labels\n\n  labels (label) get (info,show) <labelIdOrName>\n    Get label details (including counts)\n\n  labels (label) create (add,new) <name>\n    Create a new label\n\n  labels (label) rename (mv) <labelIdOrName> <newName>\n    Rename a label\n\n  labels (label) style (color,colour) <labelIdOrName> [flags]\n    Change a user label color or visibility\n\n  labels (label) modify (update,edit,set) <threadId> ... [flags]\n    Modify labels on threads\n\n  labels (label) delete (rm,del) <labelIdOrName>\n    Delete a label\n\n  batch delete (rm,del,remove) <messageId> ...\n    Permanently delete multiple messages\n\n  batch modify (update,edit,set) <messageId> ... [flags]\n    Modify labels on multiple messages\n\n  archive [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Archive messages (remove from inbox)\n\n  mark-read (read-messages) [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Mark messages as read\n\n  unread (mark-unread) [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Mark messages as unread\n\n  trash [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Move messages to trash\n\n  settings filters list (ls)\n    List all email filters\n\n  settings filters get (info,show) <filterId>\n    Get a specific filter\n\n  settings filters create (add,new) [flags]\n    Create a new email filter\n\n  settings filters delete (rm,del,remove) <filterId>\n    Delete a filter\n\n  settings filters export [flags]\n    Export filters as JSON\n\nWrite\n  send [flags]\n    Send an email\n\n  forward (fwd) --to=STRING <messageId> [flags]\n    Forward a message to new recipients\n\n  autoreply <query> ... [flags]\n    Reply once to matching messages\n\n  track setup [flags]\n    Set up email tracking (deploy Cloudflare Worker)\n\n  track opens [<tracking-id>] [flags]\n    Query email opens\n\n  track status\n    Show tracking configuration status\n\n  drafts (draft) list (ls) [flags]\n    List drafts\n\n  drafts (draft) get (info,show) <draftId> [flags]\n    Get draft details\n\n  drafts (draft) delete (rm,del,remove) <draftId>\n    Delete a draft\n\n  drafts (draft) send (post) <draftId>\n    Send a draft\n\n  drafts (draft) create (add,new) [flags]\n    Create a draft\n\n  drafts (draft) update (edit,set) <draftId> [flags]\n    Update a draft\n\nAdmin\n  settings delegates list (ls)\n    List all delegates\n\n  settings delegates get (info,show) <delegateEmail>\n    Get a specific delegate's information\n\n  settings delegates add (create,new) <delegateEmail>\n    Add a delegate\n\n  settings delegates remove (delete,rm,del) <delegateEmail>\n    Remove a delegate\n\n  settings forwarding list (ls)\n    List all forwarding addresses\n\n  settings forwarding get (info,show) <forwardingEmail>\n    Get a specific forwarding address\n\n  settings forwarding create (add,new) <forwardingEmail>\n    Create/add a forwarding address\n\n  settings forwarding delete (rm,del,remove) <forwardingEmail>\n    Delete a forwarding address\n\n  settings autoforward get (info,show)\n    Get current auto-forwarding settings\n\n  settings autoforward update (edit,set) [flags]\n    Update auto-forwarding settings\n\n  settings sendas list (ls)\n    List send-as aliases\n\n  settings sendas get (info,show) <email>\n    Get details of a send-as alias\n\n  settings sendas create (add,new) <email> [flags]\n    Create a new send-as alias\n\n  settings sendas verify (resend) <email>\n    Resend verification email for a send-as alias\n\n  settings sendas delete (rm,del,remove) <email>\n    Delete a send-as alias\n\n  settings sendas update (edit,set) <email> [flags]\n    Update a send-as alias\n\n  settings vacation get (info,show)\n    Get current vacation responder settings\n\n  settings vacation update (edit,set) [flags]\n    Update vacation responder settings\n\n  settings watch start (begin) [flags]\n    Start Gmail watch for Pub/Sub\n\n  settings watch status (ls) [flags]\n    Show stored watch state\n\n  settings watch renew (update) [flags]\n    Renew Gmail watch using stored config\n\n  settings watch stop (rm,delete)\n    Stop Gmail watch and clear stored state\n\n  settings watch serve [flags]\n    Run Pub/Sub push handler"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":64,"aggregated":"Usage: gog gmail (mail,email) <command> [flags]\nBuild: v0.13.0 (5cd913e28780)\n\nGmail\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"           Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING         Account email for API commands\n                               (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript/ads)\n      --client=\"\"              OAuth client name (s