:[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Explaining automation setup**\\n\\nI need to clarify that I can't automatically access the chat due to the absence of a token password in this session. If the user provides or stores the GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD for the OpenClaw gateway, that could enable automation. This could also include setting up a Gmail watcher. It's crucial to keep my explanation concise and provide clear options for the user to consider.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Not quite yet.\n\nRight now, **you can access Gmail in your terminal**, but **I can’t read it automatically from chat** because this agent session doesn’t have the `GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD` needed to unlock your stored Gmail token.\n\nSo there are **2 ways** to make chat-based unread checking work:\n\n1. **Quick/manual**\n   - you run:\n   ```bash\n   export GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD='your-password'\n   gog --account xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx gmail search 'is:unread in:inbox'\n   ```\n   - then paste the result here, and I triage it\n\n2. **Proper automatic setup**\n   - make `GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD` available to the OpenClaw/gateway environment\n   - then I can run Gmail checks for you from chat\n   - after that, we can even set up a Gmail watcher\n\nIf you want, I can help you do the **proper automatic setup** next.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc3952e888191ba4d37c0e56b7272\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":225,"output":261,"cacheRead":84480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84966,"cost":{"input":0.0005625000000000001,"output":0.003915,"cacheRead":0.02112,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025597500000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777124241044,"responseId":"resp_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc391644881918d91136bcb626d70"}}
