mething can’t be recovered, I should clarify that a reset or re-authentication might be necessary. It's important to highlight that no tools are needed for this process. I'll make sure my explanation is clear and straightforward, as that will help the user understand what steps to take next. It’s all about providing useful information without overwhelming them!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"You usually **can’t get it back**.\n\nThat password is just a **local encryption password you made up yourself** when setting up `GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD`. It isn’t stored somewhere readable for me to fetch.\n\nSo there are only 2 cases:\n\n1. **You remember it**  \n   - use that same password again in:\n   ```bash\n   export GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD='that-same-password'\n   ```\n\n2. **You don’t remember it**  \n   - easiest fix is to **reset the stored token and connect Gmail again with a new password you choose**\n\nIf you want, I can give you the exact **reset + reconnect** commands next.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc8c59cd0819195e2fa3f6fc29766\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":369,"output":174,"cacheRead":88960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89503,"cost":{"input":0.0009225,"output":0.00261,"cacheRead":0.02224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0257725}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777125568601,"responseId":"resp_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc8c0f36c8191b8a6545f808c0a6a"}}
