78X8WvAEArfee2WjTV655R9Rb_hA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering token reset commands**\\n\\nI need to provide the user with clear commands regarding their request. There’s no need for memory in this case, but I should consider carefully mentioning the token deletion, ensuring it’s reversible through reauthentication. Since the user explicitly asked for this information, I must ensure the process is not destructive. I’ll focus on providing a concise answer while making sure to clarify that resetting the token is an option.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes — do this.\n\n**1. Set a new keyring password**\nChoose one yourself:\n\n```bash\nexport GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD='your-new-password-here'\n```\n\n**2. Make it persistent in Codespaces**\n```bash\nnano ~/.bashrc\n```\n\nPut this at the end, with the same password:\n\n```bash\nexport GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD='your-new-password-here'\n```\n\nThen reload:\n\n```bash\nsource ~/.bashrc\n```\n\n**3. Remove the old broken token**\n```bash\nrm -rf ~/.config/gogcli\n```\n\n**4. Add credentials again**\n```bash\ngog auth credentials /home/codespace/.openclaw/media/inbound/client_secret_xxx.json\n```\n\n**5. Reconnect Gmail**\n```bash\ngog auth add xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx --services gmail --readonly --gmail-scope readonly --gmail-no-send --manual\n```\n\nThen:\n- open the Google link it prints\n- approve access\n- copy the full redirect URL\n- paste it back into the terminal\n\n**6. Test**\n```bash\ngog --account xxx_YOUR_EMAIL_xxx gmail labels list\n```\n\n**7. Restart OpenClaw**\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\nThen come back here and say:\n\n**check unread gmail**\n\nIf you want, after you run step 5 and get the redirect URL, I can help check you pasted the right thing.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e249c009ade638f0169ecc904e2f881918196b4c86b32f66e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":397,"outpu